,Recommended,242680,19591228,"Posted: 9 December, 2015",all,borf,"( Update 95)I seriously thought I'd never see the day Nuclear Throne came out of early access, but here we are after two years of constant weekly updates and support from the developers.I won't go into detail about how well they handled the early access system because that doesn't really determine the value of the finished game, but the devs are some of the best when it comes to talking to their community and being completely open about the development of Nuclear Throne, including regular streams that allows people to watch the devs do their thing. It's a wonderful example of how well early access can be used to create the best game possible, and I hope future titles learn from Vlambeers success.Anyways, the game as it stands now:ProsExtremely difficult, yet rewarding.12 (+2 secret) characters,all with unique playstyles and mechanics. Some are very basic to learn, while others are more suited for advanced players.Over 100 weapons. I felt like making the weapons aspect of this review larger because of how varied they are, but I'll just say this to sum it up: Super Bazooka.Daily and Weekly runs give the game a competitive aspect. The daily system is currently broken as of writing this review, however I'll update it when it is fixed. If the daily runs are the reason you may be wanting to buy NT, I'd wait for a while until it gets fixed.Quite possibly my favorite soundtrack of the year.Gorgeous artwork which really helps make the NT universe come to life.Yung VenuzCons:There is currently a lot of bugs in the game. Some of these are very minor texture glitches while some completey render the game unplayable on some systems. Like I said above, the developers are very much aware of these and are working on fixes right now, but I might suggest waiting until the next update comes around.This is a very controversial subject in the NT community, but keep in mind that the game is capped at 30 FPS. In my honest opinion I find this to be completely okay, and I'm usually picky when it comes to FPS issues in games. But NT is designed around 30 fps and doesn't suffer from any of the usual issues.There are some balancing issues when it comes to a secret aspect of the game after the final boss. The devs are aware of this however, and are gonna tone down some of the unfair aspects of it.Easily my game of the year, It's been a fantastic experience watching this game grow into one of the best rouge-likes of all time. My conclusion would be to wait until a future update, but if you have a need for a new rouge-like/lite, seriously don't hesistate in buying this. 200 hours in and I'm still having a blast killing various monsters with super flak cannons."
