,Recommended,242680,32410555,Posted: 14 June,all,INIGO BBY COME HOME,"Too long? Here's the short version: Very challenging game with unique characters and extreme replayability, 10/10.Nuclear Throne is a bullet hell Rogue-Like shooter with procedurally generated levels and enemies that will always keep you on your feet. You get through the game by collecting rads which are dropped by most enemies. Once you collect enough rads to level up you're given a choice of four mutations at the end of a level. These mutations will give you various buffs such as higher speed, higher health, less enemy HP, etc. Most mutations work well on their own, but some combinations are almost game-breaking. As such, there is a fair amount of theorycrafting behind the mutation system and it gives you a lot of room to try out different mutations and see which ones work for your character.Speaking of characters, the game consists of 12 different characters including the 2 you unlock from the start. These characters are incredibly diverse in playstyle and I highly recommend that you try out all of them at least once to find out who works best for you. Each character has their own unique active ability, which is used by pressing RMB on PC. These range from shields to telekenesis to vine traps. These abilities can be upgraded with a mutation unique to your character called Throne Butt. Throne But generally makes your mutations even more powerful and allows you to synergize more mutations with your active.Overall, this game is absolutely worth the price. I'd highly recommend this to player that enjoy games similar to Enter the Gungeon and other bullet hell games. However, be aware that this game has a very steep learning curve and you WILL be dying a lot. If you can get past that initial wall, you will spend hundreds upon hundreds of hours on this game topping your previous high scores and hunting for secrets."
