,Recommended,242680,19082322,"Posted: 14 November, 2015",all,Salim Sahadi il Makhmud III,"Amazing.Nuclear Throne is a rogue-like top-down action type of game, which has the player charging through randomly generated levels and fighting of hordes of bandits and various other mutated monsters.As the name suggests, Nuclear Throne takes place in a mutated world. You, the player has a choice of 12 balanced characters to try and reach the Nuclear Throne, the final boss and name of the game. In terms of gameplay, this game takes the cake. In earlier levels, things will seem boring, with safe spawns and easy victories. But progress further and you will see that things change very quickly. Later places such as the Frozen City are jam-packed with enemies, and your only hope is to keep moving.The player is also on the hunt for radiation. If you manage to collect enough, you can mutate. Each mutation has its strengths and weaknesses, and work well in specific situations, and this is what, in my opinion, gives the game an extra kick. Picking random mutations can get you killed, so choose wisely.With the many weapon choices, bosses bound to keep you on your toes and mutations that can either save you or kill you, this game can get intense. I wouldn't recommend this to people who aren't trying to game on the edge, and would rather stick to calmer titles. But for the gamers on the edge who want a fast-paced thriller, this is a much recommended game for you."
