76561197995479351,Recommended,242680,11272744,"Posted: 16 July, 2014",all,apparatur,"Buy this game! It's fun, it's rich in variety, it's interesting and it's got great music.Don't get put off by the early access lable - this is not one of those games you buy just for the promises. The game already feels finished, with a wide variety of characters to choose from. With one active and one passive special ability they all play differently, some only a little and some a lot (samurai-chicken!).Ther is new stuff to discover even after you've played for a long time, secrets to discover, new awesome weapons to find, secret rooms and so on. And the developers are doing almost weekly updates, sometimes bigger, sometimes smaller, so there is still lots of content coming on top of that.The gameplay mechanic is very simple, as you go around shooting everybody while trying to avoid enemies and projectiles. There is some character progression through various mutations, but the game is still mostly based on your skill in aiming and evading.For me it's not a game to be playing for hours on end, but rather a few runs whenever I find the time.Oh, and did I already mention the game has great music?For me this is definitely the best indie game this year."
