,Recommended,242680,21649735,"Posted: 5 March, 2016",all,Gecktendo,"Be prepared to read the words ""You did not reach the nuclear throne"" a lot.  Be prepared to accidently kill yourself when your disk gun shot richocets off a wall and back at you.  Be prepared for an adrenaline rush every time you face Lil' Hunter.In this game, you will die a lot.  It's bullet hell and you have 8 measly hit points.  Seems like it's not a problem right? Well, most shots in the game will take down half that and more.  There's no invincibility frames after getting hit, some enemies shoot powerful enough weapons that they will kill you in one shot.And yet you keep playing.There's a beautiful feel to the game.  The gunfire sounds are audibly pleasing, Every hit on an enemy is satisfying.  As you progress further, the game only gets more fun.  After looping, you begin to feel unstoppable, but eventually you get claimed and the struggle continues.  You always die in this game, but you die a little less frequently as you progress.Do yourself a favor and pick this gem up.  You won't regret it.One small note, the developers have stopped working on the game, so if you see any bugs, it's unlikely you'll get a fix for it for a long time."
