,Recommended,242680,16078310,"Posted: 30 May, 2015",all,Evan_N,"Nuclear Throne is a game that I see myself playing for years to come. It has an incredibly high skill ceiling, a huge amount of variety in characters and abilities to mix things up, and tons of options to increase the level of challenge. It's one of the few commercial games that fully captures the feeling of limitless challenge that a game like Dungeon Crawl Stone Soup does. Like Crawl, I can get to the point where I can consistently beat the game with one character over and over, but what about post-game loops? What about other characters? What about beating the game with a difficult crown?This is the kind of game where you get as much difficulty and challenge as you put into it, and I think that is what gives it the lasting appeal of the classic roguelikes. Add to that an amazing update schedule that makes early access actually fun to participate in and Vlambeer's famous style and this is easily one of my favorite games of all time. I've got just under 100 hours under my belt and the game isn't even out yet, and I anticipate putting in many more over the next few years."
