,Recommended,242680,21248907,"Posted: 16 February, 2016",all,CobaltBW,"This is the kind of rougelike I've been waiting for for a LONG time. And it's pretty ♥♥♥♥in' good.It's a fast-paced, skill-based shmup rougelike where you shoot enemies and collect items in randomly generated levels.  You're challenged to dodge projectiles, mind your ammo, use special abilities and strategically choose from a wide array of weapons and upgrades for the most optimal runs. Like most rougelikes, it's brutally hard, but what I think separates this rougelike from most of the others is its attention to balance and its surprising level of fairness. Most if not all items and characters the game offers are great for their own reasons, but more importantly, bad situations can always be turned around if you think fast; nearly every death I've ever had occurred because I was careless, didn't watch my back, or I miscalculated while dodging hellfire. There are virtually no instant kills in this game, and cheap shots just don't exist. That being said, you can expect your HP to get whittled down very quickly if you're not careful, so don't get cocky!The unlockable characters cover every character archetype under the sun (speedster, tank, glass cannon, crowd control, dual wielder, berserker, etc.), and they all play quite differently thanks to having dramatically different special abilities... the farther you get into the game, the more compelling each unlockable gets. Coupled with the weapons and upgrades (called ""mutations"") upon levelling up, this allows for a multitude of different ways to experience the game. The levels themselves are also quite varied and full of secrets.And if you want to do something a little less random, the game offers Daily and Weekly seed challenges. The Daily seed locks the map generation and mutations, and you're challenged to play through it once to achieve a high score on daily leaderboards. Weekly seeds are available Friday through Sunday and can be played through multiple times, but you're locked into a character, a special weapon and one of twelve game-modifying ""crowns"".Aesthetically and soundwise, the game is oozing with style. Environments and characters are vibrant, cartoony, well-animated and original, taking full advantage of the pixel aesthetic. The rock-oriented soundtrack is upbeat and atmospheric, followed by background sound effects for added ambience. There's no ""dialogue"" per se, but many of the ingame characters add spice to the atmosphere through unintelligable quips and one liners spoken in an alien language.If you like a challenge, random levels, and fast paced shootemup action, get this game. Like, I wouldn't even wait for a sale, it's just good."
