,Recommended,242680,20361206,"Posted: 6 January, 2016",all,MILFTANK,"I tend to repel against indie titles because most have pixelated graphics, a style I never quite enjoyed looking at.So after I finally lowered my biased opinion for once I saw a game called nuclear throne. Intrigued by it's similar gameplay like ""The binding of isaac"" which I enjoyed quite a bit, I bought the game after countless hesitations and started it up the moment it was done downloading.Man was this a breath of fresh air.This game to me was like Jesus freaking christ showing up to christian people. I never thought I would say ""This is harder than trying to sing the russian national anthem backwards without even having heard it nor the russian language once"" but here I am. If you're a fan of any rouge-like games whatsoever, then this game will certainly fulfill your dreams and beyond.The gameplay is fast, hard it will probably end pretty quick(Like me in bed)because you died but you will want to start over again because it's so addictive.The enemies will tear you apart, Your weapons will most likely screw you over in one way or another and if that's not enough the bosses will surely leave a scar on your back saying""i was here you lil shet.""The music is bloody brilliant and fills you with adrenaline, actually helping you getting through the harsh level.Even there is little to no story to be discovered in the game there are bits and pieces which the player can make his/her/it's own conclusion to what the story is about.I think this game is great. Actually no, scratch that.I think this game sets the bar for how a difficult but fair game should be. Not a complete pounding session but a pounding session with some lube. And maybe some baby powder.Also fish can roll."
,Recommended,242680,18174529,"Posted: 24 September, 2015",all,pH. mmSNAKE,"This is an isometric twin stick rouge-like shooter. You pick you character and off you go. Like many similar games environments are semi-random. You follow themes, enemies and weapons in tiers as you go but each map, amount of enemies their composition (not counting bosses) are all random. This can lead to unfortunate game over by spawning into a car (that has been patched) or in a room where you have no feasible way to get to cover or win, but hey it's a part of it. Just as getting an over powered weapon and steamrolling the opposition.With minimal amount of unlocks the draw of this game is to just be able to hop in, try your best and you are done at the end. Next time you start at the same spot but you are not likely to have the same experience. With hundred or weapons pickups, and numerous powerups to plan your run this game won't go stale any time soon.While you can get unlucky with spawns, the difficulty in this game lies solely on the player. Your decisions, both short term combat tactics as well as long term with choosing right tools for the job as you go and picking the proper or most suitable mutations. It makes it so when you die,  nine times out of ten it's on you. Always room for improvement. The game has no 'real' end. After you complete the stages you loop it with harder enemies and more new weapons.Guns are really the star of this game. It goes from the basic screwdriver and revolver to absurdity of super plasma cannon or nuke launcher. You will redecorate the level with some of these. It is really satisfying plowing through things with laser minigun or blowing up the area with super bazooka or so. The farther you get the more reward you can reap with better and more over the top toys. If you are the kind of person where the feel of combat, shooting (or swinging) makes or breaks the game for you. This fits the bill.Overall I'd add this to the list of outstanding rouge-likes that are easy to pick up, put down and be satisfied with every turn."
