,Recommended,242680,23406904,"Posted: 5 June, 2016",all,TopLel,"This is a great game, and has quickly risen to one of my favorite games of all time. There are many good things about this game. It has numerous weopons that are all a blast to use, different characters to fit all types of playstyles,it has multiple endings thorugh different bosses, but one of the best part about this game is the progression system. The first time you will play, you will die within about two or three levels depending on your skill level, which will unlock you melting. Within a few hours, you will be reaching the labs, and unlocking steroids, and before you know it, you are looping regularly, trying to kill Mom with a golden weopon to get the golden frog pistol and unlock frog or attempting to defeat the captain rith rogue to get her b-skin. The best part about this game, to me at least, is how it focuses on th gameplay over the story. Too many games nowadays try to either have a super deep story presented through dialogue heavy cutscenes or hide it through little sprinkles of information to get you to dig deeper. While this game does have some sparse lore, it never takes center stage over the main attraction, which is the balls to the wall fun gameplay. This is the first game in a while that I've seen focus on the fun the player is having over a super deep story. Lastly, the game is balanced very well. For every crap run you have where you get terrible weopons like the wrench and laser pistol and die on lil' Hunter, you will have an amazing double loop run with the fully powered up energy sword and the super crossbow. However, there is a minor gripe I have with it. There are texture glitches that occur every once in a while, that tamper with gameplay severely. Every few runs, I will have a texture glitch, where the texture that covers the level boarder shows up without hit detection. Usually its not a big problem, but multiple times i've had a run ended due to and enemy that i couldn't see such as one of the ice robots that I couldn't see throwing a car at me and ending my run instantly. That is really the only major reoccuring problem I have with the game. I reccomend this game to anyone who enjoys hard games and twin-stick shooters. 9/10"
