76561198068554358,Recommended,242680,17667663,"Posted: 22 August, 2015",all,D4NDY_,I spend most of my time on this game trying to get my characters back after each update.10/10 would spend 2 hours trying to find a skrewdriver so i can unlock Y.V again.
,Recommended,242680,30690553,Posted: 23 March,all,Candel,"A few years ago, I found myself wishing for a game where I could just gun down hordes of enemies and feel really overpowered. Then, a short while later, I found Nuclear Throne. This game is a crazy fun top-down rogue-like shooter thingy, and I love it to death.I love everything about this game. When first playing it, it's challenging, but has a satisfying learning curve to it. Getting farther and farther, finding new, creative weapons, unlocking new characters to play, and just having that feeling of ""one more run, and I can make it further than before"" was such a great time. Over time, old obstacles become easy, and you find yourself getting far every time and having crazy runs that are fun as hell. But the game stays challenging no matter how good you get at it. Even after mastering the game and unlocking almost everything, the game still poses a challenge, just in a different sense than when first starting out.The most exhilarating part of it all is that while you may have crazy overpowered weapons, you're still as frail, if not more frail, then any single enemy you fight. All it takes is a few mistakes and you're done. But dying isn't an issue, all you gotta do is hit the R key and jump back into it, and within ten minutes you could already be as far as you were when you died. Once you get on a crazy run, it's just an adrenaline rush of gunning down hordes of enemies while constantly having to keep on your toes to make sure you don't end up dead. And when you inevitably wind up dead, you can take a breather as you fight your way through the early levels on your way to another crazy run.Another amazing thing about this game I have to note is the sound. Everything in this game sounds... Satisfying. Picking up weapons, switching between them, shooting things, killing enemies; everything has a satisfying punch to it. Every enemy has a unique sound for getting hit, and for dying, so even if you're shooting at things off-screen, you still know what you're hitting and whether or not you killed them. The soundtrack is amazing, too, to the point where I sometimes listen to the songs outside of the game.The game's also got a lot of character to it. Every mutant you can play as is unique and has their own lore behind them. The universe is very interesting, and all the details about it are shown rather than told, for the most part. You learn about the world through the little details in the game, and it all adds up and is very interesting. Deep lore n' stuff. Of course, you can ignore the lore and just enjoy the crazy fun shooting parts, too.Overall, the best word to describe this game for me is ""satisfying."" It's satisfying to kill things, satisfying to reach further and further levels than your previous best, satisfying to find and master the tons of crazy weapons in the game, satisfying when something blows up and the screen freezes for a split second to add to the punch. I've played this game constantly for over two years now, and it's still kept me satisfied after all this time. The best part is that this game was and still is very affordable in terms of price, and is totally worth it. I recommend this game heavily to nearly everyone I meet.I've been regularly playing this game since December of 2014, and I don't plan on stopping anytime soon. Seriously, pick it up and give it a try, it's amazing."
