,Recommended,242680,18679204,"Posted: 25 October, 2015",all,Old Major,"I have just started playing this game after it being recommended to me by a friend, and I thought I might mention a few of the pros and cons of this game so far. Baring in mind this is early access the cons are what I recommend for the final game and should be added in for a better experience.Pros:-8 Bit Graphics are cool, keep it that way. Fits the play style perfectly.-A gradual difficulty slope that is easy enough for you to progress but difficult enought to make you want to come back for more, but I found that a few people (not including myself) found that it was more difficult than expected.-Plenty of stages and levels to progress through, but it would be nice if you were to add more as people get better at it.-Charatcers: the variety is great and all the special abilities and mutations means each run is unique and different from the last. It would be nice to see more for those who have played with every character and need something new.-No micro-transactions at this time, baring in my it is still early access there is know means of putting money into the game after you have bought it, this is good!Cons:-Not full screen, The game runs in full screen but you have black bars along the side, please remove it as it is an ugly feature and the game would look cleaner and more atractive in a widescreen view. Though this isn't the end of the world it would be nice if the game had some graphics settings.-30 FPS Cap!! What? Why? I am not sure exactly why the game devs have made it so the game can only be run at 30fps or less. Surely if the PC can run it higher (which almost any pc can) it should be allowed. This made the game feel ever so slightly choppy but it was fine overall.-Co-op can only be done in a local network. Sadly this means I can not play with friends unless I bring my pc into the same internet as theirs or play split screen with a controller. Make a means of playing co-op online with people on steam. This would make the game more tactical as you would have to work together. I think this would be a great addition for the final game.Summary:Should you buy this game?Yes, if you need some time to kill and are willing to pack in a few hours learning the characters and improving. It is worth the price especially as they have updated it over 90 times since the original release. This game has perma-death so expect to get annoyed throughout the time of playing it. Anyway I hope this review helped you make a more informed decision on wether this game is for you. Leave a like if it did, Thanks."
