76561198015015741,Recommended,242680,20488825,"Posted: 12 January, 2016",all,evil_paris,"I had to check to make sure this game was no longer in Early Access, because even finished it still feels like it isn't quite done.  Part of that is the rough art style (chosen), and part is just that your deaths are frequently very random and often unavoidable.Nuclear Throne has a lot of 1-2 hit kills, and sometimes just flat out screws you with a level starting position.  Spawn in the middle of a boatload of high damage enemies with no cover to  be had, and all your progress can melt in an instant without you really haven't any meaningful choices to make to avoid it.Similarly, if you happen to kill the final enemy on a level, the spawned portal may appear and detonate a nearby car or other inopportune object and send you to a pointless and undeserved grave.Other than a number of fairly cheesy deaths, the basic gameplay is pretty enjoyable.  The game encourages you to use the terrain as cover, and has some mild bullet hell where you weave and dodge to avoid a hail of projectiles.  There is a nice collection of different weapons to choose from, though having played Chicken extensively in beta, I'm always missing better options for melee weapons (which are great, allowing you to bounce bullets when timed correctly and trading range for unlimited ammunition).Your character gets to pick one from a few different potential mutations every time you level up.  These are not particularly well balanced, and it is entirely possible to get to choose really good mutations, or to get stuck with some completely pointless ones.   It tends to be less a matter of choosing between play styles, and more a matter of hoping you have at least one good mutation on the selection list.  Go a couple levels with all bad mutations, and your run is effectively done for, without you having done anything to deserve it.Kind of seeing a trend there.Still, there's enough enjoyable moments that it is worth picking up and playing.  I think it could have been architected to be a more satisfying experience, but it remains worth trying out.   Levels are very short, and the style of terrain and enemies changes every couple levels, so play throughs are quick and contain a mix of experiences.Go ahead and give it a run."
