,Recommended,242680,22155216,"Posted: 30 March, 2016",all,Orange Enigma,"After 50 hours with Nuclear Throne I can say with confidence it is worth the purchase. Also, I can say with confidence that I am terrible at it. This game is a bullethell-rouguelike-topdown-twinstick shooter, and it is quite good. The art is nice, and each character is balanced, although each player will end up having a favorite. The gameplay is fast. Really fast. As soon as I die I am left pondering what killed me (thankfully it tells you). You will definitely learn to react quicker and the strategies required to loop throughout your playtime with this game. Daily challenges and weekly challenges keep me coming back, and I love to participate in them. Seeing how I stack up against friends is really fun and I love seeing where I place worldwide (someday I'll be in the top 100 I swear). For the price, it is definitely worth the purchase (also the music is fantastic)."
