,Recommended,242680,29735900,Posted: 5 February,all,McCree,"Note: I received this game for free from a friend. However, it will not affect my view in any way.--Positive--Fast and UnforgivingKilling enemies is quick, dying is quick, movement is quick, the whole game has a constant reliance on fast-paced gameplay.Character varietyThere's a lot to choose from right at the start. Each character has their own abilities, look, sounds, loading screen tips and more.Weapon varietyThough not as varied as, say,Enter the Gungeon, you'll still have lots of fun finding all sorts of new weapons to rain bullets and explosions on your enemies.--Neutral--Pixel artstyleI personally think it fits the game well but others may not be so keen on it's retro look.--Negative--Difficulty spikeThe game very suddenly throws an incredibly challenging boss at you on level 5 - 3, and it only gets worse from there.30 FPS lockIt would seem devastating for a game like this to have a FPS lock under 60, but in my opinion the game is still fine with it. 60 FPS would definitely make it more enjoyable, but unfortunately the lock is tied with the engine so the devs would need to remake the game from scratch to hit it.Fast and UnforgivingYep, a double-edged sword. The crazy difficulty could keep players away as much as it could make masochists want to overcome the challenge more.Overall, i'd give this game a shot. It is a lot of fun and I really hope Vlambeer will make a sequel/spirtual successor to it."
