,Recommended,242680,19526890,"Posted: 6 December, 2015",all,SSSpeedbumpé,"Oh man.After two years, it's finally here.I'll keep this review short, for those people who want an outline whether they'll want to buy the game or not.(DISCLAIMER: I HAVE NOT PLAYED ENOUGH OF THE CO-OP MODE, SO I WILL NOT BE ABLE TO REVIEW IT)Let's begin:First off, this game is not for everyone. For the easily infuriated, this game is likely not for you (but you can always try it, if you see that it does not fit you, you can always refund it :P). You will die in this game. A lot.PROS:+Controller support.+Highly addicting.+Endless replayability.+Variety of eveything, whether it be guns, unlocks, B-skins and enemies!+Characters are fun to play, easy to learn and smooth to control.+Amazing audio design, weapons feels satisfying to use.+Dope af soundtrack (it really fits in well with every level/situation you are in)+Local Co-op.+Challenges/Leaderboards, game offers daily and weekly challenges to test you against other players.+Smooth art and animation.+Well though out lore.CONS:-Difficulty could spike really high at a certain point, disrupting the flow of the game.- Crowns could take days to unlock all of them.There is one final thing that I must address, and that is the whole '30 FPS' issue. As most people think that 30 frames is a big issue considering this is a game with a fast paced tone and low res; it really isn't. You can easily play this game hours on end and easily get really,reallyfar into the game.Nuclear Throne offers a true rogue-like and enjoyable experience for hardcore gamers and casuals alike, paired with a fair price and an amazing community to back it up.Also, one final thing, if any problems appear with the game (which rarely do), post it in the forums and the devs will surely work on a fix.EDIT: Engrish and formatting."
