,Recommended,242680,30053514,Posted: 20 February,all,Freeman1255,"Nuclear Throne takes the ""screwed over from terrain"" elements of a rouge like and mixes that with very difficult gunplay (the good kind of difficult mind you) meaning you have to utalize every weapon you can find, pick your mutations (you level up from getting rads from defeating foes) carefully and think about which one is either the most beneficial or the least ""I wasted leveling up"" kinda thing (not that the mutations are bad, its just they are random, thus you need to pick the best you can by thinking carefully even tho the mutations that may be available may not be what you were hoping to grabLasltly you need to mae every round count unlike some twin sticks which hand out health packs and ammo frequently, you have to either get lucky or keep an eye out for chests, not to mention, the chests can ""open you up"" if you will by attackingThe game feels like a mix of the binding of issac, mixed with a schmup (can be overwhelming at times and very difficult, but isn't a bullet heck) and a twin stick shooter for obvious reasonsBut this is  an interesting concept  for a game(reminds me of a mixture of rampage (ie be a monster/mutant) mixed with the nuclear post apocalptic aspects of fallout in terms of the game on the ""tip of the iceberg"" if you willBut what keeps you coming back to play the game is that it's very quick to pick up and play (or throw down and rage quit, xd) while also being fun and giving you that ""just one more run"" kind of feeling if you get a game over, and with a cool cast of characters with their own individual traits and abilities (some characters were unexpected) and plenty of replay value, this game is a great game to pick up and who knows, maybe a Nuclear Throne 2 will come around?"
