76561198031235616,Recommended,242680,12644444,"Posted: 26 October, 2014",all,kibop,"Once again Vlambeer creates one of the greatest Rogue-like games of all time! With over 100 weapons, 10+ mutations(upgrades) and , 10+ characters. This game has taken up most of my free time as it will yours. I got into this game by several Youbers including bisnap, Kakujo, Sleepcycles.This game has procedurally generated level, weapons, and mutations. I has perma-death and unlockables. The looping system in this game is very complex. So don't expect to win in your first 10 hours.As a semi-pro like myself many people are competitive and try to do the ""dailies"" , a seeded run in which you get only one chance to achieve glory on the leaderboards. The recently added dailies have preset characters, mutations, Crowns, and weapons.2 of my friends have this game and seem to have taken a linking to it. I will tell you the story of my people. Blaghs blgggagh blasgghs. Thank you Fish for that demonstration. The wraps up my review for Plutonium Chair. 10/10 Vlambeer."
,Recommended,242680,21928114,"Posted: 19 March, 2016",all,PiTMiN,"FYI I have used a different save purely to the experience the crowns, as they provide a whole new challenge all-together. It is also the reason why I have all of the achievements unlocked, where as in actuality, I have around half.****I HAVE COMPLETED THE GAME, LOOPED AND SUCH, I SIMPLY CANNOT BE BOTHERED TO GRIND FOR CROWNS****Nuclear throne is one of those games where you WILL have a love/hate relationship.Love it for its characters, setting, fantastic soundtrack, bosses and butt-ton of weapons,and hate it for its brutal difficulty and the occasional area where good runs go to die (im looking at you crystal caves).So, lets get into it shall we?Nuclear throne is a roguelike shooter set in a post-apocalyptic world filled with mutants, freaks and everything inbetween. You play as a rhag-tag band of mutants, all filled with character and personality. These mutants dream of placing their mutant butts on the nuclear throne, a myth thats believed by these guys. These mutants are special, because as soon as they die, they get teleported back by these mystical portals popping up across the wasteland.The story is simple, you choose a mutant, and you travel across the many lands filled with a variety of freaks, bandits and  floating ♥♥♥♥ing crystals. In every main area (Badlands, scrapyard Etc) you'll encounter a boss that you must slay in order to go to the sub areas (Not the official name, but something I call them). These are areas that are inbetween the ordinary, 3 level areas. These are 1 level areas that are completely different in setting to other areas and hold special enemies and loot.After doing all of this (Trust me, its a long task) and doing specific things related to things I cant say due to spoilers, you can loop. This means going aaaaaall the way back to the start, but this time its harder, much, much harder. The enemies are tougher and theres a whole new cast of bosses to slay, each one harder than the last. The loot is better, but the risk is bigger.The way collectibles go, there are B-skins for every playable mutant, unlockable by doing specific things, some hard, some are very easy. There are also crowns to unlock through playing, this is essentially run modifiers that you can aquire mid way through the run or at the beginning. They add an extra challenge for the seasoned veteran. There are also golden guns that replace some of the original guns. These special versions are found in a certain area(s) and increase certain stats of the weapon or doing specific things. Also, it shines ingame and can replace the starting pistol if you finish the area its found in.The soundtrack is one of the best ive heard ever. And ive played quite a few games in my time. Each boss has its own song to go in the backround and each area has its own song too. Its so good that I listen to the songs in my spare time.So, to break it down, heres a simpler form of what I just said for the challenged reader:Pros:Fantastic sountrackVibrant characters (That talk in their own made up language)Simple yet enjoyable storyinteresting lore (read that♥♥♥♥♥♥ its brilliant)colourful and marvelously designed areasbeautiful character and enemy designA lot of variety in enemy types and looksBosses are amazing yet challenging if not preparedBrutally hard- Keeps you on your toes at all times, even if you are just fighting a few banditsArtwork is brilliantDevs that listen to the community and are gamers themselvesCons:Some areas are more unbalanced than others (Crystal caves again...)Bugs are uncommon, but come in small sizesOften times you wonder ""What the hell just killed me""Thank you for reading, this game is my favorite roguelike, and I love it, even though my hours say otherwise.Would I reccommend this game? Without a doubt. Are there things that could be improved? Of course, but every game is like that. Its 8.99 for endless fun, anger and stupidity with the amount of loot, weapons and collectables to be collected.Thank you again for reading."
