76561198048998186,Recommended,242680,9074317,"Posted: 12 February, 2014",all,TheBytemaster,"Crazy good game. Fast, harsh, brutal, unadulterated and randomly-generated glee/rage/fun. Cannot recommend highly enough. THIS is the game that you put up on a projector and throw a party with. Tons of variety and content, (especially for a beta!) and it's only getting better as time goes. Some of my favorite highlights/features/doohickies include.;- ASPLOSIONS. Lots of 'em. Asplodey-ness is not lacking here. Cars explode, enemies explode, barrels explode, grenades and rockets and sticky bombs all explode, heavy hitting, nice solid sounds, adjustable screenshake for those who have sensitive eyes/want MOAR glory out of life; all the good stuff.- Over 50 weapons and about a bajillion combinations. Everything from shotguns to screwdrivers to laser miniguns and jackhammers. Yes, you can kill bosses with screwdrivers to rub it in if you want.- 10 unique characters, all with their own passive and active abilities. Have you ever wanted to dual-wield sledgehammers? This is the game for you.Each character totally changes the gameplay, and there will likely be one or two more released before the game is finished. Adds a ton of replay value, especially for the price, which IIRC will probably go down a bit when the game is released if you’re not into “beta” stuff. I highly recommend buying it now though, weekly auto-updates are a joy to behold and seeing the game change and grow so quickly is one of the coolest things ever.-This is -literally- the only game ever where, ""aww crap I ate my laser pistol by mistake instead of my blade gun"", is a valid complaint to make..- Mutations! 21 of them and counting. Mutate new limbs and powers on the fly! This is one of the centerpieces of the game really, and it gives it a lot of strategy and depth without being too complex.. Should you play it safe with Rhino Skin and Rabbit Paw? Or go in all guns blazing with Laser Brain and Extra Legs? You decide!- Interact with the devs! The devs are awesome and actually listen to and interact with their community. They host open-chat livestreams every tuesday and thursday where you can see what game developing is all about behind the scenes. You could easily influence the development of the game if you have an idea they like!- Nuclear Crowns! These are like mutations, but they’re harder to get and change the game in more interesting ways. For example; the crown of guns replaces ammunition drops with MOAR GUNS. (This bit is still very WIP.)- One bazillion unique enemies and three spectacular bosses (and it’s still in beta!). Lots and lots of them, all ready to cause you rage/be blown backwards at ludicrous speeds. The polish on the enemies is amazing.- Incredible sound effects by Joonas Turner. Every shot is a war cry and every explosion is a burst of life. This game is ALIVE with sounds. Each mutant/enemy even has/will be getting their own voice-overs and sound effects.- Oh right. I forgot. THE BOSSES. They rule. Intense? You've never seen intense before. Pounding music, bullet hell, death, glory, spit and grit, it's all here. When's the last time you fought a rampaging mechanical dog the size of a dinosaur? I rest my case.- Amazing soundtrack by KOZILEK. Guitars, harmonicas, heavy synths, thumping bass. There I go again making lists... Long story short; I've listened to it for 50+ hours and still love it.- SECRETS! There’s already a secret area. Pure legit-ness on a stick. Golden weapons, B-skins, secret music, all of these round out the game nicely and keep you coming back for more.- Oh, and the soundtrack is FREE! (at least for now). Just go into the folder where the game is stored and you'll find a handful of mysterious .WAV files lying around. Yeah, that's right. You're welcome. *blasts airhorn*- Crunchy 8-bit pixel-art goodness by Paul Veer, one of the best pixel artists around. Smooth animation looks great, and the characters/enemies are all lively. Did you know that the shotgun-toting alligators smoke cigars and breathe the smoke out of their noses when not fighting? Look closely, it's there.- VERY minimal system requirements. I'm running this on a 5-year-old dell laptop with a Nvidia Quadro 160M graphics chip; solid 60fps.So, that about wraps up what I think! 2 crystallized thumbs and a robot leg up!If you’re still on the fence about getting it, I’d recommend getting the FREE Mojam prototype and precursor to this game, (Wasteland Kings), and giving it a try first! (keep in mind that Nuclear Throne is about 4-6 times better)You can give that for a spin, (as well as some other amazing FREE games), athttp://vlambeer.com/3/andhttp://store.vlambeer.com/Thanks for reading!(TL:DR, this game is amazepants and you should buy it NOW.)"
