76561198010771034,Recommended,242680,9644545,"Posted: 27 March, 2014",all,metahominid,"This game is pure awesome! Despite being early on in development, unlike many other early release I haven't experienced any nasty bugs or crashes. The game itself is as others describe it ""rogue-lite""; a fast paced and intuitive rogue-like game that is easy to play and easier to get addicted to. One of the tags very fittingly describes it as a 'procedural death labyrinth'; enemies, item drops and level layouts are somewhat randomized while still following a storylike theme as you delve through deserts, sewers and icy wastelands. Gamepad support is available, though not fully supported at the moment but nonetheless capable and fun. The artistic style is simply wonderful; nostalgic and beautiful in its simplicity.The best aspect is the various and colorful characters to play; each is rather wacky but presents varied play styles. All are great fun and are difficult in a number of ways. There are certainly things that are apparently lacking but these are easily overlooked in the face of its depth, fun and most importantly the promise at such an early stage.Don't waste your time!BUY THIS NOW!7/10"
