,Recommended,242680,8957435,"Posted: 2 February, 2014",all,|αη| Baron von Bean-Jam,"I first heard of this game a long while back when it went by a different name and desired to be ""The Binding of Isaac with more skill-indexed gameplay"". Or something like that. A good many months and a name change later, I feel as though they really nailed what they were going for. The shooting is solid, projectile deviation isn't too bad and a successful playthrough to completion isn't determined by lucky item drops but by your ability. But...what exactly is this game, you may ask?This is a top down shoot-em-up roguelike that features a cast of characters with their own gameplay quirks.They have their own abilities or traits that you have to (slightly) alter your playstyle to embrace, with some making the journey to the throne a good deal easier than others. You keep fightin' till you die and then you start over with randomized levels, items and all of your traits that you gained by leveling up gone.The difficulty of this game can be described as...definitely challenging, because it wastes no time in punishing you if you make a mistake. You don't have invulnerability frames (or any that I've noticed), so you'll get quickly melted down by machine gun fire, actual fire and hordes of melee enemies. If you're not dead outright, you'll definitely be close.Speaking of death and adapting your playstyle, one of the funner things you can do is play as the Chicken.When you die as her, her head pops off and she can run around for a little while still able to attack before finally actually dying. Combine this with the trait earned through leveling up that allows you to get health for killing enemies, and you have a way to potentially be unkillable (if you're lucky enough to have it activate on a constant basis).That is but one of the wacky things you can figure out to do in this little, action-packed gem.Which, I should add, is still in early access as of this review. I greatly look forward to see where this goes in terms of balance and content addition.Amazing score / 10, will definitely play again"
