,Recommended,242680,19858254,"Posted: 22 December, 2015",all,DarkTree,"before i progress further in this review, BUY THIS GAME (but only if you're not a ""easy difficulty"" pleb)this game is hard. like, really hard. really, really, REALLY hard.as of writing this, the game has 12 unlockable characters (14, if you count super secret ones) and each one is so different from eachother, has their own advantages and disadvantages, and each one has crazy possiblities that lead to totally different runs. i'm not going to list each one, of course, but my personal starting character reccomendation is Crystal, she's pretty goodthere are 7 main levels, but it follows a certain formula; (normal level, 3 sections, final section has a boss) (transition level, no boss [except for on loops]), repeat x4, loop/win, repeat x4, etc. keep in mind, each level is randomly generated with enemies, the area itself, and the pickups and props that spawn.weapons are pretty cool, they all draw from 5 ammo reserves (bullet, shell, bolt, explosive, energy), and pickups for ammo can either be found in ammo chests or just dropped by enemies. 2 guns can use the same ammo reserve, and that means that 2 different types of ammo don't drop, just the one that you're holding. but that means if you run out of ammo for one, both are useless.there's local co-op but it's only supported by gamepad and it's pretty dysfunctional imo. then again, i've never properly played it with another personthis game has secret stuff and that means this is the kind of a game which i like to call a ""wiki-based"" game, where you constantly have to look stuff up either when you're not playing or pause and pull up another tab to look stuff up. it almost never gives you hints on the secret stuff, and when it does, it's exTREMELY cryptic. i don't mind it that much, thomutations are selected after you get enough rads (level two starts at 60 rads, after leveling up, the next level will take an extra 60 rads to get to) you get to select a mutation. mutations are passive upgrades that will usually have either next to no effect or save your life. there are a lot of them. and none are permanent, nothing is, except for charactersanways, if i had to give this game a metacritic-like score i'd give it 93/100. buy it. you may not enjoy it as much as me, but ♥♥♥♥in' buy it, bro. this game is an experience i think everyone should have."
