,Recommended,242680,17032675,"Posted: 13 July, 2015",all,rewalzzz,"Whether or not Nuclear Throne will be a fun experience for you can vary.One thing that needs to be said about this game and I feel hasn't been stated by the developer or other reviewers well enough is this: this game is very very hard. It is probably one of the hardest games you will ever play.The thing about this game is that itcanbe enjoyed by everyone, but the people that will enjoy it themostare the hardcore skilled players who want a challenge. I don't usually say this when reccomending a game, but if you are not very good at video games, you will probably not like Nuclear Throne. You can die almost instantly to just a small cluster of bullets, to one explosion, or something you didn't see which can leave you confused and angry. Trust me, that last one happens a lot. And when you die, there are no checkpoints, it's game over. Back to the very beginning.In addition to this difficulty, the game has a ton of content that is only accessible if you progress very far. Meaning if you don't do well, you won't have as much of an in-depth experience as some better players will.If you are a skilled player looking for a very challenging game that you will player for many hours, pick up Nuclear Throne. Vlambeer have done a great job at updating this game very often, so your money will surely not go to waste."
