76561198112106319,Recommended,242680,27042968,"Posted: 23 November, 2016",all,SledgeHammer [SSS SSquad],"Nuclear Throne is like Binding of Isaac, but faster. You kill more enemies faster, and you die faster. Since enemies drop much-needed health, ammo, and xp pick-ups on death, you can't hide behind cover, you have to move forward constantly.Skills and weapons combine to create completely ridiculous loadouts. My favourite skills are ""Shotgun Shoulders"", which makes shotgun pellets hilariously bounce all over the screen, combined with ""Impact Wrists"", which makes fresh corpses hilariously bounce all over the screen. Melee combat is surprisingly satisfying, with melee weapons reflecting enemy projectiles, and a combination of animation tricks makes each swing feel shockingly weighty for a 2D isometric game.This game is really ♥♥♥♥ing difficult. There is only one ordinary skill (and no pick-ups) in the game that increases your maximum health, and you have no invincibility frames when hit. Enemy attacks do high amounts of damage. Thankfully, even in later stages, enemies do not feel bullet spongey, but the sheer number of them, with some enemies firing either extremely accurate shots or spraying their attacks everywhere, poses a significant challenge."
