76561198039153010,Not Recommended,242680,20280927,"Posted: 3 January, 2016",all,Solid,"I cannot recommend this game in good faith.Those who are aware of my history with this game may find this unusual and I apologize to any who are offended by my opinion.  However I cannot, under the weight of my conscious, suggest that others play this game.  The issue is not a lack of quality; quite the opposite.  This is a game where people lose hours, days, weeks while just pushing as far as they can.  Spawn, kill, get hit by a Rhino on 6_1, spawn, kill, meet Lil Hunter, spawn, kill, loop all over again.  My time played is staggering, but I am not even close to the most time spent by a single person and it also does not account for all the additional time spent.  The hours I used making posts, talking about things with friends, watching others to see what they did, finding secrets, and getting unlocks.  Over the past years this filled gaps between less interesting games and shows.  Just a seamless gauntlet of spawning, killing, porting between worlds, collecting gats, slaying bosses, and then getting taken out only to do it all over again.  And again.  Deep in it's subtitles, simple in it's concept, hypnotic in it's nature.  A beautiful back hole of time.  If given the chance to do it again I'm certain I'd spend even more time with it...  But-but for others, for those who are not aware; who have not stood at the brink of the abyss.  Have not watched time slip though their fingers run after run; loop after loop.  I say there is nothing for you here.  If you were to delve into this it could make so many other titles appear shallow and lacking by comparison.  It's brilliance would make a library of games appear dull under the same light.Again I say; under the weight of my conscious and in good faith I cannot recommend this game.  Now if you'll excuse me I have an abyss to peer into once more."
