76561198033602078,Not Recommended,242680,19931230,"Posted: 25 December, 2015",all,Citronvand,"After seeing all those positive reviews my expectations were high. The main thing that made me refund it was the 30 fps cap, the game didn't feel smooth at all and the camera movement felt very twitchy for lack of a better word. Especially with a Xbone gamepad, it was a little better with the mouse and keyboard. My problem with mouse and keyboard was the re-binding of keys were limited, I could not use my extra mouse buttons and I could only add more bindings to the keyboard, not remove existing ones. So space will always change weapons for instance, you couldn't use space for something else, which I wanted. Well, you could but then space would do 2 things, change weapons and whatever you added, which made it unusable.The game itself wasn't that bad, but certainly not worth the ""Overwhelmingly Positive"". I expected more of the mutations, I was hoping they were unique to the characters and changed the appearence. But they were more like meh powerups, such as deal damage when you take damage, slower enemy bullets, ""extra-life"" and stuff like that. The characters didn't feel that different to each other either, each character basically has a gimmick ability, for example one character can roll and another character can pull enemies and items to him. But the gameplay still felt the same betweeen all the characters. There wasn't enough difference between them. It came down to shoot stuff with guns + 1 gimmick ability.The game didn't feel very random either which rogue-lites normally do. Generally you want a new and fresh start whenever you die. But the maps, albeit randomly made corridors, always were the same in the same order and you always encountered the same bosses in the same order. Take bindings of Isaac for instance, there is a chance you encounter boss X on floor Y, but in this game you always encounter boss X on floor Y. This, the not so different characters and the meh powerup mutations made the game feel very similar, too similar, between playthroughs. Not something you want in a rogue-lite.The game feels very overhyped and I can't recommend it at full price. I might give it another chance when there's a big discount but my impressions is that it isn't that good and the 30 fps cap stands out like a sore thumb."
