76561198087789909,Not Recommended,242680,25847831,"Posted: 3 October, 2016",all,[JPP] waddleman,"TLDR: This game has a horrible habit of being impossible to win unless you get lucky and you constantly run out of ammo. Even the most skilled player might be spawned into a room with zero cover or get caught between 2 attacks that can't be dodged without cover.This game is frustratingly difficult. In most roguelikes you get stronger over time (binding of isaac, roguelands, etc) so your experience, abilities, and weaponry scale to fight harder enemies. The problem with nuclear throne is that even though you gain more abilities as you progess through the game, you still take a ludicrous amount of damage from every enemy at every level and there's no invulnerability window after you're hit. This means about 1-2 bullets or touching an enemy 1-2 times will instantly kill you at every level. The general response is, ""Just get better at the game."" But many mobs have attacks with no gap that are only blockable with an ability, a melee weapon, or cover. So if in the moment you are shot at you don't have access to any of the 3, you die instantly. And if you're unlucky enough to stand between two enemies that fire these walls of bullets, you die instantly. Additionally the game will spawn you into a new level literally sourounded by enemies and boxed into a tiny room. So as soon as you spawn into the level, you die instantly. This makes bossfights so annoying. Almost every bossfight level is just a large arena with no cover packed with enemies. So you have about 5 seconds to franticly waste all your ammo trying to clear out the room before the boss or an errant enemy kills you in one hit. Finally ammo is balanced terribly. All useful weapons have a very low ammo capacity and use a criminally large amount of ammo every time they shoot. So your only hope of lasting to later levels is to use weak weapons that don't use a ton of ammo, or use a good weapon at 100% efficiency and pray to god there are enough ammo boxes in each level."
