us are broken. Controller support is buggy, especially in regards to the menus. Pause has a main menu button and a reset game button. Resetting the game takes you to a 1 second intro, then the main menu. Is there a point? Someone explain this to me. Before anyone bashes me for saying no to this game, someone please explain this. Why do we need both buttons? We don't. It's just their for no reason.It's a no.If you want more proof...https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3fJiVmb-vQsIts 20 mins of gameplay. The guys already familiar with the game so its safe to assume hes decent at it... fast forward 18 minutes... it's the same thing that was going on the first minute.Now, take a look at some of the comments.Thats it."
76561198066332922,Not Recommended,242680,13797515,"Posted: 2 January, 2015",all,Saltabiten,"Too hard, unplayable in the long run..."
76561198050549441,Not Recommended,242680,12270898,"Posted: 27 September, 2014",all,freedan,"I bought the game hearing that it was like binding of isaac although a little faster paced. I was looking for that casual game feel where each run would end in death (probably) but I would either progress a little farther or learn a little more about the game. This game is excruciatingly hard which makes it almost impossible to play in my opinion. But I’m gonna do this review old school and rate it by gameplay / sound / graphics and overall:Gameplay: 2/10 – Here’s why. It is way way too hard. I love games like BoI and Rogue Legacy, games where you feel you’re progressing and making headway. This game does not have that. You have a primary and secondary gun with the ability to swap out any guns you find on the level (this is where they get their two points). Each gun has an ammo type (bullets, energy, arrows, explosive or shotgun shells) and you can only carry so much of each ammo type, which is the first mistake this game makes, the enemies are crazy fast and there are a LOT of them. You normally won’t run out of ammo but if you do, it’s a wipe.Your health is very limited: 8 health points, most enemies take out two per hit, some will take more like 3 or 4. So you basically have 3 hits and you’re dead. There are mini bosses every 2nd stage and these can be difficult to take down with so many enemies on screen. As your avoiding the enemies, the shots they fire, the bosses multisprays and trying not to get to close to any explosive objects on screen, you're getting hit or playing it very safe which kills the fun of the game. It’s very hectic and seems unfair most of the time.The secondary powers your character gets is mostly unusable for most of the characters. And the one character (steroid) that has a really useful secondary power (dual wielding) starts off with 2 health points…. basically making him useless.Death comes quick and often. Too often. This game doesn’t have a learning curve so much as it has a learning scatterplot. There are a few strategies to use, but they all involve progressing very slowly, which seems out of place for such a fast paced game. Surprisingly, the first time I played this game, I made it to level 4, then after that, I had trouble getting to level 2. I think it had to do with character selection and the random guns I picked up.Sound 4/10 – It’s loud and not that great. Sorry. There is a certain ambience to some levels, but mostly it’s jarring and not the best. Sound effects are fine, and I like the SPLAT of enemies being smashed.Graphics: 6/10 – For what it is, I actually like the graphics. One of the main reasons I even picked this game up. Although the graphics are 8-bit esque, they are done well. Wish there were more variety though. Each level has 2 -3 enemy types and with there being around 7-8 levels, combined with the 10 or so characters, it just doesn’t add up to much variety. But that doesn’t mean I don’t like what I see.Overall: 3/10 – Those gameplay mechanics really drag this one down. It’s almost unplayable. Or rather it’s not fun to crawl through a game like this that is suppose to be so hectic and crazy. Those videos you see on the store page seem like so much crazy and fun-ness, but imagine the runs being as short as that video (watch the video again, and think 3 hits and I die). If you want to survive, you have to slow it down so much, that it becomes a different game. For that reason I will say the gameplay in the videos are unrealistic of what the game really is. Combine that with a sub-par soundtrack and graphics that lack the variety I expect from such a small game, it just doesn’t add up to a 10$ game. Wait for this game to go on sale for 1.99, you won’t be disappointed at that price. Let me rephrase that, you won’t be AS disappointed at that price, but I can tell you it’s not worth the 12.99 I paid for it."
