,Recommended,242680,9394641,"Posted: 8 March, 2014",all,ApachePrime,"I wish I had bought this game months ago when I first saw it. It is one of the most fun games I've played, and every update gets better and better. The devs bring a lot to the table too, with live streaming of the development progress. The characters are all unique, but similar enough that playing on Random is even more fun just to see who you get each round. There is so much more than the surface of this game suggests, and they are just adding more. Early Access doesn't mean ""unplayable"" in this case, and the bugs are few and far between. Enjoyable is an understatement, with one caveat below.Random is the key to this game. If you can't deal with that, don't play it. Every level is random. The guns, the power-ups, the enemies, all random. This game can be very tough, and unforgiving. Sometimes you'll spawn in a perfectly safe little passage way, with the enemies spaced out and strategically easy. Sometimes you'll spawn next to a boss who can kill you in one shot. Some run will give you the weapons to hold your own against ANYTHING, and some runs you'll get the same few guns over and over. I don't think the random nature is frustrating, but your mileage may vary."
