,Recommended,242680,19250314,"Posted: 24 November, 2015",all,Grabbed_by_the_spetsnaz,"Saw this game on a Youtube channel and thought it'd be a nice waste of a couple of hours.Over 140 hours later, I just keep coming back!The game is a top down shooter, where you must progress though a post-apocalyptic world, picking up bigger guns, and shooting any mutants anlong the way, very simple to pick up, very hard to master!What makes this game so addicting is the sheer amount of variations you can get.There are dozens of weapons ranging from your trusty revover, to golden crossbows, to nuke launchers, to blood cannons! The weapons are so varied and abundant that you'll never get boared finding and using them!Characters are also uniqe and special in thier own way, with great personalities to boot! Each one with a unique playstile and ""Ability"" which includes a bullet proof shield, ability to fire two guns at once, to orbital strikes and corpse detonations!That's not all, as you progress though the game you gain ""Mutations"" Which drastically change up your playstyle, suddenly you can smash though walls, send people flying into others for extra damage, and regain bullets for your minigun just by shooting people with it!But that's not even scratching the surface of content! There are B-skins, seceret levels, secret chracters (And super secret characters), acoustic B-themes for every level, secret bosses, crowns which change abilities and so much more I can't say for ruining the suprise! Just when you thought you'd seen it all, Valmbeer throws yet another curveball in to keep things fresh!Not everything is perfect though, levels are randomly generated using a simple algorithm, in which the way it creates the level can be made such a way it's impossible to shoot from safetly, single corrodors which can glitch your characters and more often than not, can place sqawn you in an area which kills you before you even have a chance to react resulting in some very frustrating moments! Fortunatly dying in this game is hardly a punishment, and you're back into the frey within seconds!Last but not all, I brought this game almost the day it's been on early access and it's been one of the best examples of develpers using it to their very best! The game has been completely overhauled several times according to the feedback they've recived, and mechanics have been redone again and again in order to optimize the enjoyment for all. It's one of the few examples of developers actually treating the early access system right and not just using it as a glorified pre-order or a way to grab cash for a game that will never be complete.TL:DR: ♥♥♥♥ing fun, tons of content, honest-to-heart developers, would recommend!"
