,Recommended,242680,21387521,"Posted: 22 February, 2016",all,AWJ,"I've put off recommending this game for some time. It's stealthy release failed to fix some prominant issues with the game at the time, but now those issues have been dealt with thanks to the long awaited update #98, I can finally say, this game is amazing.It's what I'd call a 'get-as-far-as-you-can-athon', with each run teaching you something new about the game and making you reevaluate your choices. Make no mistake this game is tough. Very tough. It demands a lot from you but is equally rewarding. This is one of the few games that I've ever experienced adrenaline rushes when playing.The cast of characters is colourful and unlike any other, the world is interesting, the weapons and the upgrades ('mutations') are all unique enough that no two runs are the same, giving this game a long life span. I'm nearing 500 hours there's still a lot I can claim to have not seen or done.The game also has a great twitch.tv community! If you're interested in the game, definately take a look on twitch.(Side note on more casual players: I had a friend who loved the idea of this game, however she's not as used to the kind of the intensity this game offers, as a result she never got far enough to see most of the game and missed out on a lot of content. She was never even able to unlock the character she really wanted to play as. So take this a word of warning, some players learn faster than others, and some may find they take a long time to 'get the hang of it'. Most would still enjoy their time learning however.)"
