76561198075282807,Recommended,242680,15958293,"Posted: 22 May, 2015",all,supersmily5,"So after hours more, many updates later, my old review of this game was VERY outdated.  They've changed alot, fixing many but not all of the problems I've had with the game prior.  There is a better menu now, although still unfinished it is a great step up; also, an in-game menu now exists whereas one hadn't before, you wouldn't believe how helpful that can be.  ""You don't know how much you'll miss something until it's gone.""  However, besides a few balancing issues fixed, they haven't made the game any easier, in fact, some of these ""fixes"" resulted in a HARDER game experience.  However, they are still working on the game so there should still be hope for the game.  The problem lies in the FACT that they aren't looking into the difficulty issue.  Through the wiki I found someone in contact with the devs of the game who confirmed that they won't even look into the issue, and it IS and issue.  It doesn't matter how great your game is if players can't get past the first few levels consistently.  Feel free to quote this, you present a challenge to your player with the INTENT THAT THEY CAN AND WILL OVERCOME IT.  You are NOT out to defeat your players, you are meant to be beaten by them.  Without a mode built in to make the game easier, a real control over the difficulty of the game, players will NOT enjoy it if they are unskilled.  It is worth noting that even I have beaten the game twice.  Both times, by luckily finding some of the most powerful weapons in the late pre-looping game early.  Both times, this was with characters Crystal (Who has a insta-shield, and therefore is the only one who can block projectiles) and Steroids (Who is yolked and can use both weapons at once, therefore is more powerful than any other character offensively), but these two wins were lucky at best, and I do not feel as though they properly reflect my skill in the game, AND THAT IS THE WORST PART OF THIS GAME.  If you are not consistently winning against the final pre-loop boss, then every win feels like it was undeserved, like you only got lucky or did something you wouldn''t normally do.  It is because of this and only this that until and unless they FIX THIS SOMEHOW, I cannot recommend this game to normal players anymore.  It doesn't FEEL fun or satisfying, it just feels like work."
