76561198075326263,Recommended,242680,17924502,"Posted: 7 September, 2015",all,QuantumJolt,"I hit the 50 hour mark so i kinda have to write a reveiw. Let me just start out by saying that this game is not for short tempered or impatient people. This game will beat you senseless only to help you back up and give you a band aid. Nuclear Throne is honestly one of the best games ive ever played. Its a retro pixel art, fast paced, rouge-like game thatll break even the most hardcore gamer's spirit. Now let me get this out of the way Nuclear Throne IS NOT a game that intentionally makes you wanna rage its actually a very well balanced and fair experiance.Nuclear Throne has you picking from 2 mutants from the very start, more can be unlocked by reaching certain stages or doing special actions and each mutant has its own unique passive and active ranging from being able to perform a dodge roll to shooting out a beam of radiation. Speaking of radiation every time you kill an enemy they will drop rads when picked up these will fill a bar at the top of the screen when filled  you will level up, this allows you to pick a mutation at the end of the level mutations are vital to your success they do things like raise your max health or increase pickup drop chance or even upgrade your active abillity or specific weapon types. When you reach level 10 aka your ultra level you can pick one of 2 ultra mutations specific to your mutant thatll which will greatly upgrade your active or passive or even add another extremely powerful passive.The game has you fighting thru multiple stages collecting rads and weaponry thatll help you reach and defeat the Nuclear Throne. Now let me just say this game has an abundance of weapons to choose from. From triple machine guns to plasma cannons or even lightning hammers this game has no shortage of ways to cut down your foes. your gonna need those guns to if your gonna deal with some of the enemys in this game. Enemys come in a vareity of colors shapes and sizes. Theres one thing that Vlambeer does extremely well and thats making things feel really good. every gun you shoot feels so nice and every hit sound is so satisfying. There is nothing better then the noise you hear when you smack a cop with a shovel. This game is an excellent example of how to make good ""game feel"".Everything has weight and the game and the feedback the game gives you is so nice and meaty. but of course lets get this back on trackNow this game isnt gonna just let you get to the Throne, no, its gonna make you work for it. youll be fighting thru hoardes of bandits, rats, robot snow gorrilas and dogs made of pure radiation. But all of those are small potatoes compared to the bosses in this game. Now let me just say that this game does bosses really well. each boss has its own attacks and patterns you have to learn and know how to counter. even after youve done that its still gonna be a bit of a pain in the♥♥♥♥♥♥to get past some of them. but when you do its very rewarding and satisfying.Now the last aspect of this game id like to address is the soundtrack. this game has and amazing one. right from the start the music really sets the pace for the game and is just all aroud the perfect theme to kick butt to. from the desert to the labs this game has a soundtrack that really holds its own. It has its own unique theme but at time has a bit of a hotline miami/ payday vibe to it and just really keeps you in sync to whats going onIn the end my hats of to JW Rami and all the other wonderful people who helped shaped this game into what it is today it may still be in early access but the games nearly finished and i think it should be this winter so defenietly get this game now or when it releases. But if your waiting for it to go on sale, it wont until its officially released. Only downside is that its still has some annoying kinks in it that need to be fixed but im sure theyll be fixed by the time im done writing this reveiw 9.5/10""Guns with six sense"""
