,Recommended,242680,18207663,"Posted: 26 September, 2015",all,His Dudeness,"Nuclear Throne is a lot like the Binding of Isaac or Zelda, but with guns, ammunition, and HP instead of items, bombs, keys, etc. It's also pretty easy to pick up and all of the characters require some sort of cognitive thought to use to their full potential. For example, Robot can break down guns into ammunition and HP, so there's a huge incentive to find every weapon case and break down any guns that you aren't going to use. Or crystal who starts with more HP and can block enemy shots for a short time. There's several different floor types, and every other architecture has a boss fight on it.As for cons to the game, I don't really have any. It has a lot of replay ability because it's RNG. I haven't invested enough time to find anything that really angers me how it works, but some of the bosses, especially first and second boss, are super easy and seem to only be a spam Mouse 1 until they're dead kind of fight, and perhaps tweaking a couple of the weapons to balance it out, because I can say I never find a reason to pick up the Disc Gun or the Flare Gun."
