,Recommended,242680,19514289,"Posted: 5 December, 2015",all,Echo Nine,"I played this game all through early access. It was updated very frequently with the devs streaming while they work. The team is super active with the community and listened to it carefully for each update.Aside from the community and the dev team being awesome, the game itself is.... REALLY good.This game is super hard and beat the♥♥♥♥♥♥out of me over and over. But once I looped (you can finish the game or choose to play through the levels again but its 5 times harder, this is called looping) I felt amazing. Then I got stomped into the ground pretty quickly. That being said you can learn all enemies patterns pretty easily after a few runs, its no the enemies themselves that makes it hard, its the combination of them.You can unlock characters via progressing through the levels or doing special things during your run(I wont spoil them). All characters feel unique and interesting and you usually always have a different feeling run with each character.I haven't even begun to explain all the other content thats in this game like different tiers of gunes, mutations, hidden levels, abilities, ect. This game has some in depth strategys with tier lists for guns and mutations if you're in to that in your rogue-like games, but at the same time you can completely ignore it and just have a blast by picking up guns that sound cool and mutations that look fun.This game is awesone and always makes me say ""just one more run I swear"". Well worth the money."
