,Recommended,242680,18870070,"Posted: 3 November, 2015",all,desertblue,"Addicting and incredibly chaotic, this game will promise equal highs of frustration and fun.  Killing hordes and hordes of enemies is remarkably satisfying, and the many different mutations, guns, and characters guarantee high replayability.  As many of the reviews have already pointed out, the game is extremely difficult, which may be a con for many people.  Many, many hours have to be put into the game before you can reach the true meat and bone of nuclear throne known as Looping.  This is where all the frustration and fun reaches a max, as you can clear hundreds and hundreds of enemies with a build of skills and guns you created (knowingly or unknowingly).  Though this is a bullet hell game, there will many scenarios in which dodging is not a possibility due to the enemy detection range and their projectile pattern. This, in addition to some rng spawns/bugs, make it extremely difficult to even progress through some levels properly.  However, the devs are still polishing/finishing the game, even and after an incredible 95 updates, it is very much believable they will sort this."
,Recommended,242680,18868725,"Posted: 3 November, 2015",all,Reldio,"Nuclear Throne is a roguelite done right. It's also a game with zero fluff, you can go from clicking start to being in game within seconds, which is a rare thing in modern gaming.Sound: Very fitting music and solid sound effects, along with neat voice clips for certain enemies and each player character. Can't fault it really, 8/10Graphics: Nuclear Throne has pretty good pixel art, though the effects for the many types of weapon are much more impressive. Stages look average. 7/10Gameplay: Tight and fun shooting with moderate RNG. Certain bosses become borderline impossible if your stage generates awkwardly, which can cause frustration. 8/10, could be 9 after more patches.Replayability: Absolutely great, many characters to unlock each with a unique ability, tons of guns to keep the shooting varied, NG+ mechanic including new bosses, skins, crowns and golden guns to unlock. 10/10Story is almost nonexistent, but it hardly matters in a game like this. Overall verdict is an 8/10, highly reccomended roguelite."
