76561198158124808,Recommended,242680,14419294,"Posted: 10 February, 2015",all,Spinnaker,"This game is incredible.First off the combat is incredibly satisfiying, the screenshake combined with that moment when you dodge your way through a hail of projectiles to hear the crunch of a wrench connecting with a scorpion means that it isnt going to get boring fast.Second -  The music is great, the tracks are incredibly atmospheric and sound perfect for a wasteland adventureThird - It has all the best parts of a rougelike:Simplicicty, replayability, a high skill cap and that sweet sweet satisfaction you get when you beat the boss or get further.But it has a trump card.Unlike most rougelikes, when you beat the final boss, you dont just start again.You loop.Looping is the mechanic of starting again with all your gear, levels and an increased difficulty so as well as the satisfaction from beating the boss you also have the challenge of seeing hoe many loops you can do, greatly increasing this games re-playability.TL;DRI have developed a reflex action meaning that whenever I die, my fingers automatically start a new game for me.11/10 would ridiculous screenshake again,"
