76561198029669648,Recommended,242680,14320885,"Posted: 3 February, 2015",all,Flower Power,"This review was conducted on 4 Feb 2015 and is subject to change as content is added to the game.Edit* love the additions to the title and in game sound track. Already warrants changing to an upvote, keep it up.This is a fun game for the first 30-45 minutes that it takes to unlock all the characters, but falls flat during the player's arduous struggle to reach the highest floor. I'm aware that this game is in early access and that things are bound to change. My issue with it is that the only replayability in its current state,  stems from the incredibly difficult task of reaching the nuclear throne. I myself have only reached floor 8 or so, but I'm finding the runs tediously repetitive rather than exciting.So many people claim that the game is similar to the binding of isaac, but with guns. I'm very familiar with the binding of isaac (Over 120+ hours between BoI and Rebirth), and I can't say that this game is remotely related to BoI other than the fact that the levels are randomly generated. What the Binding of Isaac has that this game is missing is constant unlockables that give the player a sense that they are progressing rather than grinding for nothing. Another really neat feature in BoI is the fact that the player can get thousands upon thousands of completely different item combinations that lead to unique effects and are often hilarious or overpowered.I think the biggest issue comes from the fact that this game feels like it doesn't have enough substance after you've completed the first few unlocks. After this point, there is a 4 hour (and counting) block of repetitive dying with no further unlocks or progress. The game is also missing that ability to be broken that everyone loves in The Binding of Isaac. The only way to get to the end, is to be patient and practice by doing a ton of runs. I have no issue with dying a lot, although in this case, the game may be slightly too unforgiving. You can get to the final floor with full health (not an easy task) and a single misfire of your explosive weapon or an unlucky spawn can result in your instant death from full health to zero, which is extremely aggravating.I understand that the binding of Isaac is similar in that beating the game takes a ton of practice, but BoI also has the occasional run where, due to RNG in item drops, you become the bane of all that is horrible and wreak havoc. I think that if the dev removed this parameter that inhibits you from becoming op, perhaps by adding quite a few more upgrades, I might enjoy the game more. As a sidenote idea, if each of the weapons themselves could have multiple levels of upgrades or effects (on top of the mutations), I feel that the game's replay value would go up ten fold.The game's wiki features a plethora of awesome looking weapons and cool features, but these features are hard to appreciate because of how difficult it is to access the floors that hold them. Ultimately the game is enjoyable for what it is in its current state. It has a fun soundtrack and decent pixel graphics.I look forward to future updates to see what the dev does with the game and I will gladly change my review if the game fulfills its potential."
