76561197994178591,Recommended,242680,16556855,"Posted: 20 June, 2015",all,Frosthark,"Brilliant top-down rogue-like shooter - you choose one of the dozen available characters, each with different powers, and try to progress through levels by killing everything that moves. Sounds simple, right? Well, add a load of cool weapons, hordes of deadly enemies, environmental hazards, deadly bosses, and you get a fast-paced and extremely hard slaughterfest that makes you hit the 'R' (replay) key after each death. The gameplay is supported by simple, yet enjoyable graphics and sound design. The game does have some minor problems (occasionally unfair spawning locations, hit detection glitches, bare bones UI) but is receiving regular updates, with fixes, rebalances, improvements and new content.In short, that's how action-oriented rogue-likes and Early Access titles should be made. Totally worth the money.Pros:+ Extremely solid and challenging action rogue-like gameplay+ A dozen playable characters, each with a different ability+ A ton of cool weapons and deadly enemies+ Simple, yet effective graphics and sounds+ Regular updates containing fixes, improvements and new content, with numerous new features to be added in the future+ Local Co-op (online Co-op may be added later)+ Fish can rollCons:- Starting level spawns will occasionally cause you to die unfairly- Limited UI (for now, it's being improved)- Some minor bugs (e.g. problems with registering hits near walls)"
