,Recommended,242680,17458131,"Posted: 9 August, 2015",all,nacon,"This is a game that I pick up and play every day - for about 20 - 30 minutes per day. Nuclear Throne is a ""rogue like"" top-down action shooter. The world you are playing in is procedurally generated, which, while following general rules, will vary every time in terms of layout and enemy difficulty.The game is very much a bullet-hell/twitch based game; if you don't like fast-paced shooting action, this isn't the game for you. Some characters, like the Chicken, can slow down time and make the game a little bit more manageable while you learn.As you shoot/slash/explode your way through the levels with one of a dozen unique characters, you gain XP for traits that power your character up and pick up new weapons to better shoot your way through the world. This also lends itself to a different experience every time that you play. When you die - that's it. You have to start over again. But it's not such a huge loss - since maybe you'll luck into that golden combination that gets you all the way to the Nuclear Throne!The game is capped at 30fps, but I don't think this detracts from the gameplay at all. The visual style is unique, and very evocative of 16-bit gaming consoles.I reccommend this game, as it is a great value for its price."
