,Recommended,242680,22900601,"Posted: 10 May, 2016",all,"Ya Boy, Paradox","PARADOX'S NUCLEAR THRONE REVIEW FOR COOL DUDESGAMER PROTIP: skip to bottom of review if you wnat veredictVery few ""roguelikes"" (hate that term lol) tend to stand the test of time, and many become boring and repetitive quickly. This thankfully isn't the case with Nuclear Throne, which is one of my favorite games to date.Not very complex, you know? Spawn in ♥♥♥♥♥♥ desert, shoot some mutant mofos, advance to the nuclear throne, holla holla get dolla. That's what makes it fun, ese? You get quickly into action, but ya also die quickly in action. For real this game grabs you by the balls as you try to master it. I don't like the comparison between hardcore and casual vidya cause that's for neckbeards like who cares lmao, but NT I'd rate pretty far up there as a hardcore game, you gotta think fast, shoot fast, pop pop no time to lose ya dig.Mechanics are simple, as you advance levels, you obtain better guns, and get some whack♥♥♥♥♥mutations to wreck some more♥♥♥♥♥♥ It's as video-gamey as videogames get, and if you're tired of all the pretentious narrative crap then yeah you got the opposite right 'ere ♥♥♥♥boy. You can dunk thousands of hours learning new sick strats to impress all the cool kids on da hood, or just mess around with silly builds (dude 2doubleminiguns lmao).It does have its drawbacks doe. First of all its made on gamemaker which as we all know it's more barebones than a bucket of KFC after a one-night-stand with Gabe Newell, so it does tend to get very buggy at times, plus it's 30 fps for all ya weenies who care about this fancy computer crap. I myself make my daily life using a 10 fps laptop toaster about to die, but that's another topic.TL;DR yeah boy if you want real fun arcade twitchy action for RAD DUDES to shoot up mutants and over all have a hecking fun time, yeah this is for you dog.I rate it 9,2/10 SICK IRONIC MEME HATS"
