76561198091387761,Recommended,242680,7989209,"Posted: 9 December, 2013",all,AsianMagick,"This is one of the funnest games I have ever played and, as of right now, it's not even fully complete yet. For me, the appeal is in being able to simply pick up the game and just start playing. You can fit in small 15 minute sessions or just keep playing for the whole night. The premise is simple: survive, shoot anything that moves, and keep going.Each world has its own unique set of enemies and they have different attacks and all the weapons have different properties. And if that wasn't enough variety, there are a bunch of different characters to play as with their own unique special abilities that are activated with the right mouse button, have their own passive bonuses.The developers constantly release updates to the game, pretty much on a weekly basis. They also interact with the community and are constantly listening to the feedback that the community gives them. Those are some big pluses in my book.Is this game hard? Absolutely. You may stop playing from some frustration.... but then you'll come right back for more. I say give this game a shot, its worth the money."
