76561198134487166,Recommended,242680,12428464,"Posted: 9 October, 2014",all,AR,"Nuclear throne is the first succesful real-time rogue-like. Never before has this crossbreed succeded. It has many good elements of rogue-like, while it manages to keep the thrill or real-time shooters. You've got different weapons, many classes, and of course permadeath. Each time you will play, the levels, monsters and the loot will be randomly created.There is a huge variety of weapons, and each one has a different feel.  Shotguns are great in close quarters, crossbows are great for long-range kills. Even the starting weapon can be deadly if you use it correctly. Melee weapons mix well, as they don't depend on ammo, can take out a cluster of enemies and can be used to deflect bullets. What is more important, is that using the weapons is incredibly fun.There are about dozen different classes (characters), each one alters the gameplay significantly. For example, there is a specialized class for melee weapons, and another one the can blow corpses. The leveling system is nice, you get a perk after finishing a level and collecting enough XP (radiation). It is a bit annoying that you get to choose from four randomly selected perks, instead of giving the players to freedom to build their own class.From a technical point of view, even though the game is in early access stage, it has no bugs at all, and it has weekly updates. The graphics are 8-bit retro, but quite nice. The music is nice as well.The game is quite difficult (I haven't managed to finish it yet). At first you need to learn to play the game, understand its logic. Once you do, 10% of your deaths will be caused by your own mistakes, and 90% by a bad level design. Let me explain, each time that you start a new level, you are located in a random position. Sometimes, you will surrounded by enemies and will have no chance of surviving. Now, dying because of your own mistake or lack of game understanding is one thing. Dying due to an RNG is another, which will either cause you to rage or to shrug your shoulders. From my understanding, this could have been easily fixed by building an initial ""safe room"" at each level. Unfortunately, the community is outraged at a mere mention of this possibility(!). Hopefully, the developers will listen to the voice of reason.===Summary====Go ahead and buy this game, if you like rogue-likes, a bit of challenge or real time shooters, you will not be dissapointed."
