76561198086364259,Recommended,242680,20538140,"Posted: 15 January, 2016",all,Baphomafyew,"Nuclear Throne is the best game I've played in many years. I love almost everything about it. However, as with most games to which a community is given Early Access, the matter of full release left a sour taste in some mouths. I will try to explain my reasons for including this in the review, but by and large the takeaway from my thoughts should be: THIS GAME IS BRILLIANT, BUY THIS GAME. It’s a more addictive, faster Binding of Isaac, and I say that as someone who returned to video games after 15 years purely because of BOI. During Early Access, the team diligently provided weekly updates which corrected, evolved and modified the gameplay and game features based on the feedback of the community. The community itself was galvanized by an independently run high-score ranking site ‘Throne Butt’ (The creator of which has now, in 2016, been brought onboard the project to run the official leader boards) which brought fierce competition for the overall top 30 high scorers as well as a place at #1 in the dailies. It would be remiss to not mention the fact that the dailies themselves have, as of the writing of this review, been broken for over a month now. We have been assured that this will be fixed. By and large, the developers are very willing to make the necessary efforts to fix bugs and correct imbalances— though perhaps understandably this willingness has diminished since the unfortunately rushed release date forced by SONY and the PS4 release of the game. This has caused a fair bit of annoyance for long term PC players of the game, who quite rightly regard the PS4 incarnation as a passing fad as opposed to the PC version which, with its strong community and Twitch.tv streamers like SleepCycles and DevilAzite, has much greater chances of being a long-lasting enterprise. All in all, the game is great, as I’ve said, and if the few instances of polishing required (the dailies and weeklies don’t work at all; the game crashes at random for a many players despite a plethora of fixes attempted by the community; textures are improperly layered, especially blood explosions; weapon sprites have rough extra pixels; bolt weapons can be fired through terrain; the mutation Gamma Guts only works some of the time etc.) are implemented promptly, it will definitely go on to be a rogue-lite equivalent in quality, value and depth to other classics of the genre, such as BOI, Spelunky, COTND and Rogue Legacy."
