,Recommended,242680,11863270,"Posted: 25 August, 2014",all,Killious,"Before going into my impressions of the game, I'd like to take a moment to address an issue that many gamers are struggling with right now. Early Access. There have been plenty of games that have burned customers throughout it's relatively short existance thus far. I am here to assure you that this will not be one of the games that evaporates into the ether. The devs have done a wonderful job of not only releasing weekly updates but actually streaming those updates on twitch! I give them major kudos for this and it's one of the things that made me decide to buy into Nuclear Throne while it is still in Early Access.Now, on to the gameplay. This is an extremely addictive game. Let's just get that out there right from the begining. Nuclear Throne absolutley nails the ""just one more run"" feeling. I frequently find myself planning on doing just one quick run and then realize a dozen runs later that I'm about to do ""just one more"". To me this is what the essence of these games is. It's quick, addictive, fun and keeps you coming, gladly, back for more.The weapons are diverse and fun and the shooting is satisfying. The game is brutally unforgiving and you can find yourself going from full health to dead in no time flat. That's one of the things that is appealing in this emerging genre of the ""action Rouge-lite"" or simply ""Rouge-lite"" or even ""Procedurally generated death labrynth"". Another thing that is appealing is the number of characters that you can play pretty much right after your first or second run.  Virtually every class is available to you almost from the time you boot the game. There is not a huge grind to unlock the next class. The only class that is not immediatly easy to unlock is the mystery class.In short, I wholeheartedly endorse this game and I hope that you will consider supporting these awesome devs as they strive to make Nuclear Throne the best that it can be!"
