,Recommended,242680,13791964,"Posted: 2 January, 2015",all,Zap Blaze,"simpy put, it's one of the best twinstick shooters i've ever played. great soundtrack, good visuals, good design, randomly generated levels, tons of characters with their own strengths (and only one with an actual weakness, thank god), quirky weapons once you get past the second area, steep difficulty curve, roguelike elements and a level up system....if i had to describe it, it's like a better binding of isaac, with a better soundtrack and a better level generator.... and better controls. eat your heart out, isaac.to this game's credit, though, it doesn't really just hand you upgrades at random like isaac does, either. it gives you weapons and ammo. you earn your upgrades by leveling up and then you get to PICK between four at random. no upgrade has a drawback. that doesn't make the game easy, though ,because after the first world, it starts to look more like a bullet hell with enemies sprinkled around than a twinstick shooter.this game is HARD. but it's challenging. you get better. you go farther. it's what a good game is supposed to do, which is  condition you through practicing with its mechanics. that's the difference between a game like this and a game like.... isaac or  in some cases risk of rain.. those games give you success based on random factors for the most part. you need to have a good setup to guarentee you can go far. this game gives it to you based on your own skill and your ability to react quickly with precision. the better you get, the farther you go. consistantly.that's not to say those games are bad or not fun. they're a couple of my favorite games. but this game takes the roguelike formula, applies it to a twinstick shooter, and makes you play it like a platformer. it's a marvelously well put together game, and i wholeheartedly reccomend it. don't let the pricetag deter you. it's one of the best games on steam right now, hands down. it's just a little difficult with a pretty average starting point that ramps up to insanity very VERY quickly."
