,Recommended,242680,13816245,"Posted: 3 January, 2015",all,JtTorso,"A lot of people like to compare Rouge-likes to The Binding of Isaac, so I will too. It's a lot faster than Isaac, while runs do tend to last about the same amount of time there is a lot going on in Nuclear Throne, you have to worry about which enemies to take out first, find your ammo boxes, rads (exp), and any weapons all while dodging bullets. There are many guns and they're all very distinctive and different and all have advantages or disadvantages, there are also mutations that work as perks when you level up. Much like Isaac this game is HARD, it is not an easy game at all, you will die many times before you progress, it's a good challanging game. Finally, this is a very light game, it's very easy to pick up and play for a little while until you die 5-6 times and quit for an hour and then repeat knowing mutations and weapons is good but it's not like Isaac where you need to know everything about every item incase your Quad Shot messes up your Poly (original Isaac).In short, this game is easy to learn, easy to pickup, and is a good challange."
