76561198085797884,Recommended,242680,13837237,"Posted: 4 January, 2015",all,IamnotJackieChan,"It's a top down shooter that has the vibe of an old nes game, but the style and finesse you would expect from a modern release. I really like the pixel art in this game, and overall the game provides a unique atmosphere with its art direction. The gameplay is straightforward, but challenging. It is a permadeath game. If you die, you have to start over. Just like old school Mario, except you only get one life. You DO get health, but it is not very much. It is set in a post apocalyptic wasteland in which you play as one of many ""mutants"" who are trying to reach the Nuclear Throne.There are plenty of characters, each with their own unique active and passive abilities to help you survive the almost always overwhelming hordes of enemies (One has a shield, one can slow time, one eats guns for bullets and hp). While blasting your way through the levels you will accumulate radiation from defeating enemies and opening containters. This radiation is what you use to level up your character. Upon leveling up you can choose from four randomly selected ""mutations"" on the loading screen for the next level, which apply passive abilities to your character to give you an advantage while fighting through the wasteland.One of my favorite parts of this game is the multitude of weapons. There are assault rifles, shotguns, a crossbow, and... Well I don't want to spoil the surprises too much, but there may or may not be various laser weapons. There are also melee weapons, which are actually very useful because they can deflect enemy bullets.The weapons chests, weapon drops, mutations, enemy ratios, and levels are randomly generated. Sometimes you start out behind cover, and sometimes you start out surrounded by enemies who proceed to instantly slam you. Sometimes you wind up with sweet weapons and mutations and sometimes you get the ones that you don't want or don't really apply to your character. Sometimes there is just no way to dodge a bullet or get out of range of an exploding car even though you just beasted through six levels without a scratch, and you have to start... All. Over. Again. Sometimes this game will destroy your soul and make you cry yourself to sleep, but with a dead look in your eyes and tears streaming down your face you will pick yourself up and whisper, ""One more time."" Because this game is well done. the character animations, character skills, enemy types, and weapons are very diverse. The art style is great, at least if you are a fan of pixel art, and the gameplay is simple and enjoyable."
