,Recommended,242680,22055199,"Posted: 25 March, 2016",all,Catspaw Fhynne,"Before I even begin this review- YES, this is worth your purchase in a multitude of ways.You're going to like this game if you're the type of gaming enthusiast that refuses to give up or let difficulty halt your progress. The game always finds ways to keep you on your toes while you develop your own set of unique skills that identify you as a NT player, as there is usually no ""true"" way to play the game due to the variety of weapons, items, and characters at your disposal.That being said, lemme just go over what I think are the PROs and CONs of this game.Pros:+The feeling of satisfaction after trumping an iron wall standing before you is great with this game.+Practically all situations in the game are capable of being negotiated with BULLETS. There can be unfair situations and conditions presented to you, but that's the name of the game- just use your brain and try to scrape through it.+Most likely one of the best twin-stick shooters of this year if not the past five years.+Game mechanics (Leveling up, RNG based spawning, portals) are unique and presentable in a non-confusing manner.+Endless hours of content+Rewards experimentation+Great developer feedback, but... (see below)Cons:-Insanely difficult to the point where it can hamper a newbie's experience, especially in later stages. Do not let it fool you- there is ALWAYS something harder waiting on the other side of a portal. Planning in advance is key to survival.-Developers have an unstable edition on PS Vita and PS3, to which they have reported that they were ""working on it"", yet has been 3+ months with no fixes in sight. Purchase this edition of NT, as it's the optimal experience.-Game breaking crashes still exist on the PC, most having solutions.-Bosses can rarely spawn/get caught out of bounds, which they will then suffocate and promptly die immediately.-No cursor lock for windowed"
