,Recommended,242680,27774920,"Posted: 26 November, 2016",all,Infinite Spookiness,"Nuclear Throne is a sizzling hot roguelikelike action game where you are fighting things in a weird post-apocalypse with increasingly exploding or weird guns (or sometimes not guns at all). The setting is seemingly very inspired by the likes of Gamma World and consequently the characters you can choose to play (along with their various abilities) tend to be quite odd. The starting two before you unlock anything for instance are a fish man and am ambulatory hunk of crystal.Overall this is pretty fun and fast, it loads quickly and moves smoothly so dying is no big thing if you want to get back into the action. Furthermore they now have Daily Challenges and Weekly Challenges, keeping things fresh and interesting as you compete for places on the boards, the Daily Challenges tend towards ""one chance at a specific instance, using whatever character you choose (that you've unlocked))"" however the Weekly Challenge is a fair bit more interesting and allows multiple attempts at a specific instance but in this case what you start as and what your circumstances are, are pre-selected for the challenge, making things interesting!Overall I recommend if you like high octane mouse-and-keyboard shooty roguelike action."
