,Recommended,242680,27464409,"Posted: 25 November, 2016",all,Corporal JinkJonks,"This game is fantastic. I absolutely love it, despite kind of sucking at it.-WeaponsThe weapons in this game have an amazing variety while still being balanced by difficulty. Essentailly, different weapons can only drop after you have cleared a certain number of levels,  raising the difficulty to the weapon's requirement. From the pistol to the super plasma cannon to (ugh) the disc gun, each weapon is distinctly useful in different situations and ineffectual in others.-CharactersEvery character has a passive and an active ability. For instance, the first character, Fish, has a passive that makes every ammo pickup give a little bit more ammo, and an active that lets him dodge roll. It's pretty easy to unlock new characters, and there are skins and crowns that take a significant amount of skill to unlock (for the completionists).-StoryThe story of this game is somewhat up for interpretation. Essentially, the characters are trying to reach the Nuclear Throne, as legends/rumors have told of its ability to fix the apocalypse. Various loading screen messages and secrets lend more insight to this, but that is the overall plot.I love this game, and I think that if you are remotely interested in it, you should BUY IT."
