,Recommended,242680,27883062,"Posted: 27 November, 2016",all,LiQuiD FuSioN,"My all-time favorite pixel-style arcade shooter right here!It's simple and fun, easy to jump in for a few quick rounds of blowing up baddies. There are times where it can be frustrating due to the difficulty, but it's hard to get too mad because that's the idea behind it all. There are no save points or anything to hold your hand. It's up to you to keep trying and learning new techniques if you want to advance.I love the charming pixel-style graphics for one, even though it may be a bit over-done in the current market. The music and sound effects are well done even if I play my own music for background noise. Overall it feels like a solid product with no glitches either that I've seen. Part of me doesn't want to reach the Nuclear Throne since I thoroughly enjoy just jumping in and playing for the heck of it. It's not a game one would spend hours at a time on, but it's works so well if you want to kill some time in short bursts. It's like my fun alternative to playing Tetris (any platform really), Space Invaders, Binding of Isaac or Geometry Wars. Definitely will be playing this one for many more hours to come!"
