76561198062368001,Recommended,242680,22510081,"Posted: 18 April, 2016",all,Dr. Daddy Ted,"Nuclear Throne is an extremely fast paced, randomly generated, top down shooter that is in the end, marketed to people that may enjoy a challenge. If you're looking for a fun experience under a pretty cheap price, I think that you will get that from this game, but be warned, Nuclear Throne is one of the hardest video games to master and conquer fully. If you're looking to play it casually, you probably won’t get too far without putting it down forever, as it does take a while to get the handle of if you're not an avid gamer and is extremely unforgiving to mistakes. To reiterate, it's not like the game can't be played casually, it's just that it probably won’t serve as a source of enjoyment for people that only want fun from a video game, as it is very centered around the challenges to overcome. Now that I've covered that, let's start with what I actually think of the game.Nuclear Throne is essentially what could be described as a roguelike, similar to such experiences as Spelunky or The Binding of Isaac, but with an enhanced focus on the gameplay and less focus on the more methodical feel that the aforementioned games operate on. Nuclear Throne doesn’t have any items like you would find in either Spelunky or Isaac, but purely functions on a leveling system and random gun drops, all of which feature different abilities, and all of which are very fun to use and experiment with. The game is also very well known for its difficulty, and is in combination with its music and art style what make Nuclear Throne a unique experience from any other game. The amount of polish to make this game feel unique is very present, and the final product absolutely shows the amount of care that the developers put into making it.I would not say that this game is not without its flaws, such as the late game still needing some huge overhauls and some final aspects being added to make for a smoother experience, but I think that it still serves as a good challenge and enjoyable experience in the long run. Considering it's as cheap as it is, I would consider picking it up if you like the type of genre that the game belongs to."
