76561198001570498,Recommended,242680,21691549,"Posted: 7 March, 2016",all,Gods Will,"Will you reach the nuclear throne?I hope so cuz I sure haven’t! This is a rather hard one where you will die and die often. It gives me that unending feel of determination where every failure you learn something new and you always make it just a little farther then you did last time. It’s cut from the same cloth as Binding of Isaac so if you like that you’ll probably enjoy this.Notably enjoyable differences however are a smaller pool of upgrades but with the trade-off of the upgrades being really good and game change in a lot of respects, especially when synergized with other upgrades. You also get to choose from a list of 4 every time and let me tell you, it’s rarely ever easy when it comes which one to grab. Enemies have a lot of complexity to them and analyzing how they move, when and how they attack and their own personal quarks leads to a rather fully realized environment. Characters are radically different and gear toward drastically varying playstyles.  even doing the beginning of the game over and over again never feels too easy and there is always enough danger to keep you alert and on guard.There are a few issues here and there. some enemies have frustrating abilities that can be tricky to remember in the heat of constant action, unlocking hidden characters requires some backward moon logic to discover (I looked it up and I recommend you do too) and every character, even the ones with more health feel like they got glass for bones and certain hazards can instantly kill you no matter how much health you got!The whole game feels like a literal wasteland. The worlds gone to hell and it’s up to you to attempt to navigate a cruel and uncaring world. If that sings to you then give this a shot. See if you dare reach the throne!PS. there is a character that makes air horn sounds and he’s the best for that single reason"
