76561198058152243,Not Recommended,242680,21857175,"Posted: 15 March, 2016",all,tarage,"After playing this game for a few months, I'm ready to write a review. Nuclear Throne is a rogue-like shooter, so if you're looking for brainy challenges, this is not your game. There are no saves, so forget about making incremental progress. Each game is an all-or-nothing race into oblivion. Oblivion? Yup, because you will die, again, and again, and again, and never make any progress. And after months of playing this, I can honestly say it's one of the most frustrating games I've ever played because I can't get any better at it. Perhaps this is a personal problem, but I can't think it's purely a personal problem. I've never made it past level 5-3. I've seen crowns once. So, if you're looking for a sense of achievement, this isn't your game. Nuclear Throne does have funky retro graphics, addicting gameplay, decent music, and a great sense of immersion. For casual gamers, it's worth the money. Just don't expect it to be something it's not."
