,Not Recommended,242680,20593466,"Posted: 17 January, 2016",all,BR | I'll Show You Passive,"Tried really hard to like this game.  I'm a big fan of Rogue-likes, difficult ones, even; got the Real Platinum God achievement on Binding of Isaac Rebirth, but this game takes it a tad too far.  The difficulty, for ME, is just plain too cheap to be enjoyable.  It's the type of difficulty where you're playing a platformer and there's spikes on almost every floor tile.  The game is a classic example of cheap-shot or aritifical difficulty - there's traps all over the place that will insta-kill you with very little or no time to react whatsoever.  There's even monsters that can fly from offscreen moving 20-30 tiles per second and can kill you instantly.  You can chalk that up to planning and strategy, which may work for you, but for me, it just leaves a bad taste in the mouth.Some of this difficulty comes from bad decisions on the developers' part; being planted in near impossible situations, unfair boss spawns, for example.  Genuine difficulty and unfair difficulty are two different things.  One can argue that unfair difficulty adds to the experience and sense of accomplishment, requires more planning, strategy and luck, but I tend to disagree, it's just a cop-out.There is a boss called ""Li'l Hunter"" (sue me if the spelling's wrong) who will just jump down from the sky with no warning and probably instantly kill you with his ultra powerful shockwave.  Cool, i've played the game a few times, maybe now that I know his entry I can prepare for it.  Nope.  On his stage, you're likely to be dropped into a large open room surrounded by 10-20 dangerous enemies with no route of escape.  Once the boss appears, he flies around the screen like a maniac, spamming all kinds of overpowered weapons, WHILE YOU STILL HAVE TO DEAL WITH THE ENEMIES THAT ARE PART OF THE LEVEL.  Some of these situations would require a complex computer running complex scripts solving their own complex formulas to successfully navigate said situation.  This type of difficulty is not fair even for a Rogue-like.You may have fun with this game being that it's action packed and (loosely) follows the Rogue formula, and the game feels pretty fun to play overall, but the artificial difficulty ruins it for sure.  I wouldn't recommend."
