76561197978500423,Recommended,242680,13852927,"Posted: 5 January, 2015",all,Live To Tell,"This. Game. Is. RIDICULOUSLY AWESOME. @_@It is insanely easy to pick up, and easy to lose an hour playing. It's execution is pretty simple: Run and gun and run and gun and run and gun some more. I would call it a '7/8 top-down view' shooter with mouse-aimed firing. Randomly generated levels from specifically theme tilesets with enemies generously and liberally strewn about so there's PLENTY to shoot at and the scenery (at least the shape of it) is usually fresh and different. And the challenge gets MADDENINGLY DIABOLICAL! Yet, it will kick your butt again and again without leaving you feeling unwanted or uninvited.It's not ""You died. You suck. You should go away and play hopscotch where it's safe.""It's more like: ""OOOHH!! TSSSSS! Sorry bout your luck there, champ. Why don't you have another go, real quick? You can do it. You made it further that time! Whattaya say, pal?""And then, before you know it? The fifteen minute session you initially planned for, has turned into an hour long campaign of awesome, leaving you questioning your actual ability to perceive the passage of time. O_O;Character-wise? They deliver exactly what they promised. A handful of rag-tag, downtrodden, QUIRKY and loveably adorable radioactive horrors to choose from. Each one plays and handles differently with their own unique perks and special skills! You level-up by mutating as you go by nomming up all the funny little glowing green tic-tacs of radioactive material from EVERYTHING you kill and even from stockpiles along the way. When you level up? You get to add a new mutation (i.e. a character perk) from a randomly generated assortment of 4 to choose from to make your little mutant-murder-machine far more tactical and survivable. Lemme tell ya, there's really no bad option to choose from when it comes to mutations, and I'm pretty sure I STILL haven't seen all of them. You will likely find plenty of perks that satisfy your sense of priorities and playstyle as a gamer. But let me give you once piece of advice, based upon my own experiences:Throne Butt. Always take 'Throne Butt'. It's uniquely different for every character and supercharges their individual character skill for even more awesomeness. :D (Throne Butt gave me a new sense of resepect for Melt. WHOA!)I could go on and on for a while about this game..... Really. But I'm gonna stop shortly, because if you've had the attention span to read down THIS far? You, personally, deserve a cookie.I haven't discovered everything. Heck, I probably haven't discovered HALF of everything yet. And I LOVE IT. The game is fast-paced, exciting, and engaging. It REALLY is something special in this current climate of rampant indie developed rogue-likes flooding the industry.Nuclear Throne stands out from the crowd. I play it regularly. I love it. I cannot recommend this game any more highly than I do. AND? It just keeps getting BETTER as they refine it from player feedback.The Nuclear Throne glows enticingly on the horizon! Pursue it!"
