,Recommended,242680,24489295,"Posted: 23 July, 2016",all,Gamertron7500,"You play the game. You're dead. You try again. You're dead. You try again for the third time. You're dead. You try again for the four- wait a minute. Now they're dead!Yes, Nuclear Throne is at its core with its retro gameplay of you playing as a mutant by wielding a variety of weapons, and killing enemies and bosses as you try to reach the Nuclear Throne. Don't expect the game to go easy on you as it just throws you in an area with various enemies and surprises for you to kill and encounter as you collect weapons, ammo and rads from them (also including chests and rad containers) as you avoid getting killed, which you will experience a lot, during the process. Only one question remains: can YOU reach the Nuclear Throne? Or will you suffer non-stop deaths that's always lurking around the corner?A fun, retro game made by Vlambeer that created Super Crate Box."
