76561198095015490,Recommended,242680,20646709,"Posted: 20 January, 2016",all,Mama Crumbs,"So as of writing this review, I've put 10 hours into Nuclear Throne. This wouldn't be as impressive if I had gotten it longer than a couple days ago, but that's what actually happened. And I have to say, I absolutely love the crap out of this game. Is it utterly unforgiving? Absolutely will punish you for any slight mistake? Does it often require nearly-frame-perfect imputs to avoid dying horribly? The answer to all of the questions is a definite yes.Despite this, I love this game. Why? Because it's unforgiving, but certainly not unfair; I view it similarly to how I view Dark Souls (which I do not have on Steam, but do have on Xbox 360, and on which I have about 200 hours). The sheer sense of satisfaction every time you beat a boss is absolutely overwhelming. You'll very quickly learn what weapons you like, what ones you don't, and which ones are best for each situation. Every character has a massively different strategy, with one commonality: as the game likes to remind you, don't get hit! Everything from a character with powerful defense to one that can break down useless weapons into ammunition, each character hugely changes up your playstyle - and when you find that character that you absolutely rock with, that's when the steamroll begins.I've not yet gotten to the throne - but I have high hopes for all of you! Go for it, and may the rads be with you!"
