,Recommended,242680,28768011,"Posted: 28 December, 2016",all,Yung Johnny's Karate Class,"Nuclear Throne is a special kind of game. The one that you always rage at but keep coming back to. Here are my thoughts on it.Cons:- The frames. It usually isn't too much of a problem for me but the frames being locked at 30 for a fast rogue like game was not a good choice.- Balance. This goes for both types of this issue. The weapons or characters are either too weak or too strong or sometimes both. Weapons like the disc gun and the screwdriver become useless because they just don't give you any benefits. Characters like Crystal have no downsides whatsoever and end up being the go to which neglects the other characters.- Difficulty. Difficulty is usually a good thing. A game needs challenge so playing it is meaningful but this game sometimes flips that whole thing over. For example, if you spawn in a level with enemies all around you right off the bat you cannot escape. This game needs lightning fast reflexes and is like hell in boss fights like Lil Hunter.- Looping. As soon as you loop, you're ♥♥♥♥ed. Random enemies everywhere who instakill you. It's a cluster♥♥♥♥.Pros- The bosses. They are fun to fight and satisfying to beat since they give you new items. They also have cool designs and are very hard (for the most part).- Weapons. So many of the weapons in this game are awesome and creative. You go from a revolver to a quadruple machinegun and you have a gatling nuke launcher at your disposal. That is some crazy♥♥♥♥♥♥- Characters. They have their own unique perks that are useful, but are not overpowered except for a certain purple pile of♥♥♥♥♥♥- Music. It's great and really fits with your kicking of♥♥♥♥♥ It can go from peaceful to intense and helps make the tone of mutants shooting things up greater.Verdict? It's good. Not perfect and not spectacular but it is a good game. It requires patience and reflexes because this is an extremely unforgiving game that will kick you back to level 1-1 no matter if you've reached the throne or not."
