,Recommended,242680,17356639,"Posted: 2 August, 2015",all,Artificial Renegade,"""You did not reach the Nuclear Throne""If you love metaphorically bashing your head into a brick wall to find out which one will break first, then this game is for you.This game, being a rougelike, will kick your teeth in and throw you in at the deep end, and leave you to fend for yourself. After you get the hang of the movement, weapons and other such stuff, you might just reach the Nuclear Throne (Yes, it DOES exist.)+There are many characters, weapons and mutations, allowing for many different combinations of favoured strategy, such as being a reckless murderer as Chicken.+The developers are usually more than welcome to feedback about the update, seeing as this game is in early access at the moment.+Co-op for pairing up to find the Throne.-Co-op camera normally focuses on P2, forcing the players to stick close together if they want to explore the map.-Cursed weapons are typically from the lower difficulties, dissuading players from picking them up most of the time.-World 3 boss is almost impossible to keep asleep during World 3-3.+/-The crowns, while giving some benefits, come with downsides that sometimes balance out the pros and cons, but more often than not the downsides are more hefty.+/-Golden weapons don't have too much of an incentive to collect, except for being able to start with a different weapon, or just having more ammo upon the start of an attempt.+/-The spawns still arent perfectly safe after recent updates, but they are much safer than before.Tips:Be wary around cacti, skulls, pipes, cars and other environmental obstacles when using grenades.Crystal cannot block every type of damage with her shield.Never forget about Melting's active ability to detonate corpses that destroy projectiles and damage enemies.Steroids can fire weapons fully automatically, no matter what weapons he is holding.If you eat a cursed weapon as Robot, you will take a large chunk of damage (As of n